Nissan to Double New Car Sales in S. Africa, Financial Mail Says

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-05-11T11:19:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/nissan-to-double-new-car-sales-in-s-africa-financial-mail-says.html
Nissan Motor Co.’s South African unit
wants to double its new car sales in the next five years,
 Financial Mail  reported, citing local Managing Director Mike
Whitfield.  Nissan  South Africa  plans to sell as many as to 900 Micras
a month after selling 551 in 2010, the Johannesburg-based weekly
magazine said, quoting Whitfield. Nissan’s manufacturing plant
in Pretoria could be building 100,000 vehicles a year by 2016,
the magazine reported, citing Gilles Normand, the Nissan vice
president in charge of Africa, the Middle East and  India .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Renee Bonorchis in Johannesburg at 
 rbonorchis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
